<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-383-740  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 383 740.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  April 23 1990 n587 p4(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>FCC changes ruling on 18-GHz DTS band. (Digital TerminationService)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Costlow, Terry.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Companies will be able to install wireless local area networks(LANs) using the 18-GHz DTS bandwidth, thanks to a rule changemade by the Federal Communications Commission that allowscommunication between nodes of a network.andP;  The 18-GHz DTS band,long in use for transmitting low-power radio signals, previouslyhad no capabilities for node-to-node communication.andP;  With the FCCrule change, the DTS band is now suitable for current networkingapplications.andP;  Motorola, which submitted comments to the FCCduring the research and decision period, intends to be one of thefirst to introduce products that utilize the band.andP;  A spokesmanfor the firm says it plans to release a product in late 1990.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Motorola Inc. (product development).andO;Topic:     BandwidthGovernment RegulationProduct DevelopmentUnited States. Federal Communications CommissionWireless Networks.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>